  "local_port": 34600,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How one can apply for IIMs after cat results?",
  "response": "After receiving your CAT results, applying to the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) involves several steps. Here\u2019s a general guide on how to proceed:\n\n1. **Review CAT Scores**: Once the CAT results are out, carefully review your scorecard, which includes your overall percentile and sectional percentiles. This will help you determine which IIMs you can realistically apply to based on their cutoffs.\n\n2. **Shortlisting IIMs**: Each IIM has its own criteria and cutoffs for shortlisting candidates. Research the specific requirements of each IIM, including past year cutoff trends, to identify the ones you are likely to qualify for.\n\n3. **Apply to Non-Common Application Process (CAP) IIMs**: While your CAT application includes most IIMs, some may require additional steps or fees post-results. Check each IIM's admission notification on their official websites for any specific application procedures or deadlines.\n\n4. **Participate in the Common Admissions Process (CAP)**: For some IIMs, there is a common process for the next stage of selection (usually for newer IIMs). Keep an eye out for CAP notifications and register if applicable.\n\n5. **Prepare for the Next Rounds**: Once shortlisted, prepare for the next stages, which typically include:\n   - **Written Ability Test (WAT)**\n   - **Group Discussion (GD)**\n   - **Personal Interview (PI)**\n\n6. **Submit Required Documents**: Be ready to submit necessary documents like academic certificates, work experience certificates, and any other documents required by specific IIMs.\n\n7. **Follow Deadlines**: Each IIM will have its own timeline for the subsequent rounds. Ensure you are aware of and adhere to all deadlines to avoid missing out on opportunities.\n\n8. **Await Final Admission Offers**: After the WAT, GD, and PI processes, IIMs will release final admission offers based on a composite score that considers your CAT score, academic performance, work experience, diversity factor, and performance in WAT/GD/PI.\n\nRemember to check the official websites of the IIMs you are interested in for the most accurate and updated information regarding their specific application processes and requirements.",
